A strange light flashed, and he actually saw Mao Zedong. Xiao Yang (surprised and excited, hurried forward): "Chairman Mao, is it really you? I am so honored to see you!" Mao Zedong (smiled kindly): "Children, it is fate to meet here. You see this tree full of kapok, red so warm, this kapok ah, like those martyrs who shed their heads and blood for the revolution, has a clank of iron bones, which is also the city flower of Guangzhou, highlighting the revolutionary spirit of the city of Guangzhou." Xiao Yang (listening carefully, nodding): "Chairman, can you tell me your life story? I especially want to hear it." Mao Zedong (with deep eyes and memories): "I was born in a peasant family in Shaoshan, Hunan. When I was a child, I witnessed the suffering of the people, and I was determined to change all this. When I was young, I studied everywhere, seeking the truth of saving the nation and the people. Later, I participated in the founding of the Communist Party of China, led the Autumn Harvest Uprising, established the Jinggangshan Revolutionary Base, and led the Red Army to break through the Kuomintang's encirclement and suppression. On the Long March, after hardships and obstacles, it finally took root in northern Shaanxi. During the Anti-Japanese War, led the people of the whole country to resist foreign enemies. After the victory of the war of liberation, the new China was finally established. All my life, I have been fighting for the happiness of the people and the liberation of the nation." Xiao Yang (full of reverence): "Chairman, your ambition is too great! What do you expect from our secondary vocational students?" Mao Zedong (earnest): "children, you secondary vocational school students are an important force in national construction. You must learn professional skills well, no matter in which position, you must keep improving. Remember, practice makes true knowledge, and you must have the courage to apply what you have learned to practice. It is necessary to maintain the spirit of hard struggle, not afraid of hardship, and grow up through training. We should also have lofty ideals. We should not only look at the present, but also link the personal development with the destiny of the country, and contribute our own strength to the construction of a socialist country." Xiao Yang (answered firmly): "President, I will try my best to do it! What do you expect from the city of Guangzhou?" Mao Zedong (looking at the trees full of kapok, thinking): "Guangzhou is a city with a glorious revolutionary tradition and the source of China's modern democratic revolution '. The people here have the spirit of brave struggle, just like this kapok, perseverance. It is hoped that Guangzhou can continue to inherit the revolutionary spirit, play a greater role in socialist construction, and become a pioneer city leading economic development and cultural prosperity. Make good use of their own advantages and constantly innovate to make people's lives happier and happier. Children, your generation should shoulder this responsibility." Xiao Yang (eyes firm): "Chairman, you rest assured! We will live up to your expectations, make Guangzhou better, make the country stronger!" Suddenly, the light flashed again, and Mao Zedong's figure gradually disappeared. Xiao Yang knew that everything just now was not a dream. With Mao Zedong's entrustment, he was determined to work hard in the days to come.
